📌 Project Proposal – Student Local Jobs Board

This is my current understanding of the direction for the project, as there does not appear to be a formalised plan in place yet.
To ensure we can move forward productively, I’ve outlined a proposed MVP structure below.

⸻

🎯 Goal
Create a web platform that helps students at:
	•	Wolverhampton
	•	Telford
	•	Walsall

find current local part-time and casual jobs.

⸻

🔹 MVP Scope (Simple & Achievable)
	•	Students can browse jobs
	•	Filter by campus + job type
	•	Click an external apply link
	•	Employers/admin can post jobs
	•	Admin approval required before jobs go live

Not included in MVP:
	•	CV uploads / in-app applications
	•	Messaging
	•	Notifications
	•	Complex matching systems
	•	Overengineering

⸻

🔹 Tech Suggestion (Basic & Safe)
	•	Frontend: React or simple HTML/CSS (Bootstrap acceptable)
	•	Backend: Node.js (Express) or Python (Flask/Django) — team preference
	•	Database: PostgreSQL (recommended) or MySQL 8

⸻

🔹 Team Roles (Proposed)
	•	Me → Database design (ERD, schema, constraints, seed data, example queries)
	•	Backend → API endpoints
	•	Frontend → User Interface
	•	Project coordination → Task tracking & delivery

